HEADWORD: Anta
<hw>An"ta</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Ant⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A species of pier produced by thickening a wall
at its termination, treated architecturally as a pilaster, with capital
and base.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Porches, when columns stand between two
<xex>ant⟦ae⟧</xex>, are called in Latin <xex>in antis</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

